OL,3,CRetired shopkeeper told he is not
OL,4,CBritish after 46 years in UK
OL,6,FHe married a British woman and ran his
OL,7,Fown business, a newsagent called
OL,8,FNelson's News, in , on the .
OL,10,FWhen that relationship ended, he
OL,11,Fmarried another woman from the UK and
OL,12,Fthey had two sons together.
OL,14,FAfter retiring he came to apply for a
OL,15,Fpassport and was told he was not
OL,16,FBritish, that means all his
OL,17,Fcontributions to the country were for
OL,18,Fnothing.
